<br>
<br>
In all seriousness though, the only class that I TRUELY fear as a rogue, is an SK with skills.  Darkness is hard to chain resist, and if they have a nice MoSS or 2 H weapon, with HT up, I can pretty much consider myself toast.<br>
<br>
A prepared mage (with pet and dmg sheild up) is kinda scary too if he gets the jump on ya.  But if you have good FR, can fear the pet, and pumice off his dmg sheild, you can kill him.<br>
<br>
Rangers- If a snare lands, and he has a nice 2 hander and good jousting skills, he can be dangerous.<br>
<br>
A Rogue with high resists, fast connection (I'm only on 56K Dial-up, but still deadly vs. Casters) and good skills can be very deadly.<br>
<br>
A wizzard will take your lunch money in a couple nukes without good FR and CR.<br>
<br>
Warriors- Dangerous if they have good jousting skills and a nice 2 Hander.<br>
<br>
Monks- See rogues (they don't scare me as much as a good rogue though)<br>
<br>
Shaman- If played well can be scary (though I've been doing quite well against them lately)  All about MR and CR + casting interrupts<br>
<br>
Necros- Can really hurt you if played well.  Easy to shut down as a rogue though.<br>
<br>
Paladins- Laff*<br>
<br>
Clerics- Laff*<br>
<br>
Enchanters- Laff*<br>
<br>
<br>
*Laff- (No offence to the classes referenced) about 70+ MR will shut these guys down for the most part. <p><font size=4 face=Times New Roman, serif><b>Ceescrit Bossalini</font><BR>
