Magic -- assuming that a rogue would have that fairly high, I wouldn't even bother with Turgur. If a blind sticks, it's a lot of trouble -- it would give enough time for Malisement and then Turgur<br>
Fire -- uuh, level 1 nuke, never mind<br>
Cold -- I don't even remember what my cold nuke does, but I think my evocation is lagging about 20 levels behind<br>
Poison -- EBolt is very nasty. Combined with SoW it makes it possible for a shaman to kite a rogue, if it sticks<br>
Disease -- Plague is worse than EBolt, just takes a bit longer<br>
Shaman pet is not too mighty, but will prevent sneaking and hiding<br>
Another thing is that a lot of shamans lately go for very high AC (I've read of 1000-1100 ac shamans at level 55). That's nasty.<br>
Before Rage was nerfed, an AC shaman would be an interesting opponent against a rogue... Shaman would be regenerating about 40 points per tick, plus whatever shirt they have :) <p><img src="http://www.geocities.com/xirinia/sig.jpg">
